Class TreeNode

java.lang.Object
TreeNode
public class TreeNode
extends java.lang.Object
TreeNode class. Each instance of this class represents an instance in a Huffman tree.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Zdenek Plesek

    • TreeNode

      public TreeNode()
      Creates a completely empty instance of the TreeNode class. The tree is not considered final, it does not hold any content. The tree is considered to be root, since it has no parent node. Occurrences are initialised at zero.

  • Method Details

    • makeAddress

      public void makeAddress()
      Call this method on root node after the tree has been created to assign all nodes addresses. It will recursively call methods in its child nodes until the final node is reached.

    • occured

      public void occured()
      Call this method to increase occurances by one.

    • generateOutput

      Returns:

    • generateOutputContent

      public byte[] generateOutputContent()
      Call this method to generate byte array containing bytes representing all this node and nodes it contains. Recursive function. '{' encoded with US_ASCII represents beginning of a node. Followed by two nodes contained wherein before it is closed by '}' encoded with US_ASCII representing end of a node. '-' encoded with US_ASCII represents final node. This character is always followed by a byte which represents content of this final node.
      Returns:
      byte[] array representing all the nodes.
